      • visitEncodedQualities

        public final void visitEncodedQualities(String encodedQualities)
        Description copied from interface: FastqRecordVisitor
        Visit the encoded quality values for the current fastq record. If the fastq file breaks the quality values across multiple lines, then encodedQualities will be the concatenation of all of those lines with all whitespace removed. This method will not be called if FastqRecordVisitor.visitQualities(QualitySequence) is used instead.
        Specified by:
        visitEncodedQualities in interface FastqRecordVisitor
        Parameters:
        encodedQualities - the encoded quality values as a single line string; will never be null.
        See Also:
        FastqQualityCodec

      • visitQualities

        public void visitQualities(QualitySequence qualities)
        Description copied from interface: FastqRecordVisitor
        Visit the the actual quality values (not encodedc) for the current fastq record. This method will only be called if the fastq implementation does not encode the quality values. This method is only called on specific fastq formatted files (for example MAQ encoded bfq files) and method will only be called in FastqRecordVisitor.visitEncodedQualities(String) is NOT called.
        Specified by:
        visitQualities in interface FastqRecordVisitor
        Parameters:
        qualities - the actual non-encoded quality values; will never be null.
        See Also:
        FastqRecordVisitor.visitEncodedQualities(String)
